By Omololu Ogunmade in Abuja President Muhmmadu Buhari Wednesday swore in four new permanent secretaries in the State House before the commencement of the weekly virtual Federal Executive Council (FEC) meeting. The brief swearing-in ceremony took place before the commencement of the weekly virtual Federal Executive Council (FEC) meeting in the council chambers. The swearing in of the four new permanent secretaries brought the number of permanent secretaries sworn in by Buhari in the past one month to 16. The new permanent secretaries are: James Sule (Kaduna); Ismaila Abubakar (Kebbi); Mrs. Ibiene Patricia Roberts (Rivers) and Aliyu Shinkaffi (Zamfara). Here are images of the event.       